			<![CDATA[<b>Ken:</b>	Sarah Kovac?  Do you remember me?  I’m Ken Springer, from Carlton College. 
<b>Sarah:	</b>Ken!  Hi!  Long time no see.  How have you been?
<b>Ken:</b>	Really great, thanks.  I just opened my own bakery this year.
<b>Sarah:</b>	A bakery?  But I thought you <blank word="were going to become"/> (<i>become</i>) a singer.
<b>Ken:</b>	I thought I <blank word="was going to sing"/> (<i>sing</i>) for a living, too.  But now I do it just for fun.
		It’s hard to make a living as a singer. What are you doing these days?  I remember 
		you <blank word="were going to live"/> (<i>live</i>) in Bangkok for a while. 
<b>Sarah:</b>	Actually, it was my brother who <blank word="was going to move"/> (<i>move</i>) to Bangkok, and he did.  
		My cousin and I <blank word="were going to look"/> (<i>look</i>) for jobs in Paris, but there was a 
		change of plans.  My parents had had a restaurant here for a long time.  Remember? 
<b>Ken:</b>	Uh huh.
<b>Sarah:</b>	Well, they <blank word="were going to sell"/>(<i>sell</i>) it, but I talked them out of it.  I wanted to keep it in 
                the family, so I’m in charge of it now.  
<b>Ken:</b>	Wow.  Who could have imagined that both of us <blank word="were going to run"/> (<i>run</i>) businesses! 
<b>Sarah:</b>	Yeah, I know. ]]>
